<h3>cHAPTER 3 tHE CHAR tYPE</h3>
<p>Initially character is intended to describe individual characters but now this is no longer the case.</p>
<p>I have worked in content based industry which uses it very extensively. Initial when java is developing at that java team  </p>
<p>happily agreed on 2 bytes or 16 bit to store a chararcter based on assumption that 65536 numbers are more than enough to represented characters </p>
<p>However, it turned out that the 65,536 characters possible in a 16-bit encoding are not sufficient to represent all characters that are or have been used on planet Earth </p>
<p>A character is just an abstract minimal unit of text , it does not have a fixed shape (that will be glyph) and it does not have a value.</p>
<p>"A" is a sysmbol simlary (U+20B9) and in html &#x20B9; is unicode for rupee sysmbol</p> 
<p>This article is good on UTF 8 Read it one more time http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/articles/javase/supplementary-142654.html</p>
